Package pl.put.poznan.transformer.buildings

Class LocationComposite<T extends Location>

  • java.lang.Object
    • pl.put.poznan.transformer.buildings.Location
      • pl.put.poznan.transformer.buildings.LocationComposite<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - Class of the location object
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    LocINT
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    Building, CompoundLocation, Storey
    public abstract class LocationComposite<T extends Location>
extends Location
    LocationComposite is the base abstract case for all of the Locations in which other locations can be. It makes default implementation for all of the Composites in the Composite design pattern. It also implements LocINT interface as in Composite design pattern is mandatory.
    See Also:
    Location, LocINT
